net.openhft.chronicle.bytes

Interface RandomDataInput

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Bytes<Underlying>, BytesIn<Underlying>, BytesStore<B,Underlying>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractBytes, AbstractBytesStore, HeapBytesStore, HexDumpBytes, MappedBytes, MappedBytesStore, NativeBytes, NativeBytesStore, NoBytesStore, PointerBytesStore, ReadOnlyMappedBytesStore, SubBytes, UncheckedBytes, UncheckedNativeBytes, VanillaBytes

    public interface RandomDataInput
    This allows random access to the underling bytes. This instance can be used across threads as it is stateless. The thread safety of the underlying data depends on how the methods are used.

      • readUtf8

        default <ACS extends Appendable & CharSequence> long readUtf8(long offset,
                                                              @NotNull
                                                              ACS sb)
                                                       throws net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.IORuntimeException,
                                                              IllegalArgumentException,
                                                              BufferUnderflowException
        Truncates sb (it must be a StringBuilder or Bytes) and reads a char sequence from the given offset, encoded as Utf8, into it. Returns offset after the read Utf8, if a normal char sequence was read, or -1 - offset, if null was observed (in this case, sb is truncated too, but not updated then, by querying sb only this case is indistinguishable from reading an empty char sequence).
        Type Parameters:
        ACS - buffer type, must be StringBuilder or Bytes
        Parameters:
        offset - the offset in this RandomDataInput to read char sequence from
        sb - the buffer to read char sequence into (truncated first)
        Returns:
        offset after the normal read char sequence, or -1 - offset, if char sequence is null
        Throws:
        net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.IORuntimeException
        IllegalArgumentException
        BufferUnderflowException
        See Also:
        RandomDataOutput.writeUtf8(long, CharSequence)

      • readUtf8Limited

        default <ACS extends Appendable & CharSequence> long readUtf8Limited(long offset,
                                                                     @NotNull
                                                                     ACS sb,
                                                                     int maxUtf8Len)
                                                              throws net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.IORuntimeException,
                                                                     IllegalArgumentException,
                                                                     BufferUnderflowException,
                                                                     IllegalStateException
        Truncates sb (it must be a StringBuilder or Bytes) and reads a char sequence from the given offset, encoded as Utf8, into it. Returns offset after the read Utf8, if a normal char sequence was read, or -1 - offset, if null was observed (in this case, sb is truncated too, but not updated then, by querying sb only this case is indistinguishable from reading an empty char sequence). If length of Utf8 encoding of the char sequence exceeds maxUtf8Len, IllegalStateException is thrown.
        Type Parameters:
        ACS - buffer type, must be StringBuilder or Bytes
        Parameters:
        offset - the offset in this RandomDataInput to read char sequence from
        sb - the buffer to read char sequence into (truncated first)
        maxUtf8Len - the maximum allowed length of the char sequence in Utf8 encoding
        Returns:
        offset after the normal read char sequence, or -1 - offset, if char sequence is null
        Throws:
        net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.IORuntimeException
        IllegalArgumentException
        BufferUnderflowException
        IllegalStateException
        See Also:
        RandomDataOutput.writeUtf8Limited(long, CharSequence, int)

      • compareUtf8

        default boolean compareUtf8(long offset,
                            @Nullable
                            CharSequence other)
                     throws net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.IORuntimeException
        Compares the UTF-8 encoded char sequence, written in this RandomDataInput at the given offset, with the given char sequence. Returns true, if they are equal. Both char sequences (encoded in bytes and the given) may be null.
        Parameters:
        offset - the offset in this RandomDataInput where the char sequence to compare is written
        other - the second char sequence to compare
        Returns:
        true if two char sequences are equal
        Throws:
        net.openhft.chronicle.core.io.IORuntimeException - if the contents are not a valid string.
